{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwaLrFi5zvZZhwSthuwx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WqGBMfcRFesrLfMivHQbXd","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2v2-f46b83c8-without-lessons-ledger--ll1-r2/memory/staging-debug-swallows-errors.md","content":"---\nname: staging-debug-swallows-errors\ndescription: Staging config with DEBUG=true silently swallows errors — check it first when errors vanish\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nWhen errors seem to disappear with no logs/output in staging, check whether the staging config has `DEBUG=true`. On 2026-07-11 a bug took ~2 hours to track down because DEBUG=true in the staging config silently swallowed all errors, hiding the real failure.\n\n**Why:** A swallowed-error setting turns a quick fix into a long blind hunt — no signal points at the actual bug.\n\n**How to apply:** When debugging missing errors/silent failures in staging, verify the DEBUG flag before chasing the symptom deeper.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1101,"cache_read_input_tokens":20506,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1101},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccc7a66-4ee0-4812-ae73-1c5d2d011eff","uuid":"6ce4a1a0-319f-4345-bdc4-8087bf8accbc","request_id":"req_011CcwaLp6yQzncbKudc6PF5"}
